@startuml
title Orchestrator state and AppStage writes

state NotStarted
state InProgress {
  state "currentPath : OnboardingPath" as Cur
  state "currentStepIndex : Int" as Idx
  state "callStack : ArrayDeque<Frame>\n(internal — not in OnboardingPlanState)" as Stack
}
state Completed
state Skipped

[*] --> NotStarted : init when AppStage == NEW
[*] --> Completed  : init when AppStage in {DAX_ONBOARDING, ESTABLISHED}

NotStarted --> InProgress : requestFirstStep()\nfirst eligible step in main path

InProgress --> InProgress : onEvent ->\nAdvance / SwitchTo(path) / Return / Stay
InProgress --> Completed  : Advance exhausts main path\n(callStack empty)\n[userStageStore.stageCompleted(NEW)]
InProgress --> Skipped    : AbortPlan\n[onboardingSkipper.markOnboardingAsCompleted()]

note right of Completed
  AppStage moves NEW -> DAX_ONBOARDING.
  Reactive CTAs (CtaViewModel) take over.
  CtaViewModel.completeStageIfDaxOnboardingCompleted
  later writes DAX_ONBOARDING -> ESTABLISHED
  (orchestrator never writes that one).
end note

note right of Skipped
  AppStage forced to ESTABLISHED.
  Matches FullOnboardingSkipper today.
end note

note left of InProgress
  SwitchTo(path) pushes (currentPath, currentStepIndex)
  to callStack and runs path from first eligible step.

  Advance walks currentPath; off-end pops the stack
  and resumes caller at indexAtJump + 1.

  Return pops a frame and resumes caller similarly.
  Empty-stack Return is a programming error.
end note
@enduml
